fix(net/http): recycle socket + drop NET lock around route() — 5 endpoints live

Three bugs found via live QEMU testing:

1. close() right after send_slice() raced the FIN ahead of the data.
   smoltcp emitted FIN before the queued response, so curl saw "empty
   reply". Drop close() from the server side; the Connection: close
   header makes the client drive the close. Server only calls close()
   when state==CloseWait (client FIN seen), to emit our matching FIN
   and reach Closed.

2. Single persistent listening socket got stuck in TIME_WAIT after the
   first response, blocking the next SYN. Fix: when state==Closed,
   remove the socket from the SocketSet and install a fresh listener.
   Tracked via static Mutex<Option<SocketHandle>>.

3. Deadlock when api_net()/api_dns() re-locked NET while tick() still
   held it. Refactored tick() into 4 phases:
     a) Hold NET briefly: poll, drain RX into a local Vec, read state.
     b) Release NET. Handle Closed/CloseWait state transitions.
     c) Without NET held, run route() — handlers can re-lock NET freely.
     d) Re-lock NET to send_slice() the response.

End-to-end verified in QEMU (full sweep, all 5 endpoints respond):
  GET /api/uptime  -> {"uptime_ms":7500,"ticks":750}
  GET /api/mem     -> {"used_kib":47836,"total_kib":130944}
  GET /api/net     -> {"ip":"10.0.2.15","gw":"10.0.2.2","dns":"10.0.2.3","dhcp":true}
  GET /api/procs   -> []
  GET /api/dns?host=example.com -> {"host":"example.com","a":"104.20.23.154"}

Also added kernel/scripts/test-http.sh: scripted boot + curl sweep for
regression testing under WSL+QEMU.
